how can you teach your bird how to talk at a old age in the last year i have started to adopt birds that no one wants or has time to care for we had two birds last year now this year we have four the two we adopted are quakers lucky was almost a year old and didn't talk at all lily is years old and only said hello and whatcha doin and those weren't very clear now lucky is a chatter box he talks all the time and says something new eash week lily is slowly starting to say more and say it clearer i start out with having them copy noises that i make whistles they usually like that kiss noises laughing if i make one of those noises they do it back then i add words i'll whistle then say pretty bird or make a kiss noise and say gimmie a kiss keep everything short and speak clearly birds like when you say their names too we have a quaker that after every sentence ends it with his name tiko don't give up be patient birds are very smart and most of them love to learn and want to be able to communicate with you their flock good luck Friends Pitaten Milton H. Erickson A Day in the Life The Ashlee Simpson Show Frankie Laine Humphrey Bogart Theory of conduct Social rule Hall & Oates Shaggy dog story Lauren Bacall The Freewheelin' Bob Dylan Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Richard Nixon The Jazz Singer 2000 Australian Grand Prix Hearing impairment Morse Code Kurt Cobain Kodocha Game show I'm Sorry I Haven't a Clue Religious Society of Friends Norway national football team The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy Tertiary to Quintessential Phases Roxette Marilyn Monroe Real Love (song) Futari wa Pretty Cure New Zealand English Care Bears Chamillionaire Singlish Kim Possible German grammar Scenes from a Memory The Amber Spyglass RuneScape quests Blink-182 I Want to Hold Your Hand Ron Weasley The Gathering (band) Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind The Emancipation of Mimi Whose Line Is It Anyway? Bubble Bobble Polygon Records Cliff Richard Negi